-- Tropical Storm Alex Forms in Caribbean, Heads Toward Yucatan, U.S. Says
-- Dick Schumacher
-- 2010-06-26T09:06:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-26/tropical-storm-alex-forms-in-caribbean-heads-toward-yucatan-u-s-says.html

          
          
             Tropical Storm Alex, the first storm
of the Atlantic hurricane season, formed in the Caribbean today,
the U.S. National Hurricance Center said today.  
 Tropical Depression One was raised to tropical storm
status, the Hurricane Center said. The storm is heading west-
northwest toward Belize and Mexico’s Yucatan Peninsula, the
Hurricane Center said.  
 The storm is about 220 miles (355 kilometers) east of
Belize City. Maximum wind speeds are about 40 miles per hour (65
km/hour), the Hurricane Center said.  
 The storm may affect efforts to control BP Plc’s oil spill
in the Gulf of Mexico.  
